snippet.title: Pray For Those In The Storm (Barron Trump Singing)
snippet.description:
Pray For Those In The Storm

Check us out on Spotify! https://open.spotify.com/album/3y1CZVxPBVqYl2ljdNVWno?si=lLRWLYbeQcuXD9TQDeKi7A

⬇️⬇️⬇️ Watch more videos below! ⬇️⬇️⬇️
https://youtu.be/WBHJZs8ZeFQ
https://youtu.be/GAdihLnAiXk
https://youtu.be/SZZW8YMZlMg?si=kP7ZE5s5fhhjjpX2
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hq_JjAodbY0

Lyrics:
[Verse 1]
The winds have roared, the skies turned black,
Homes are gone, they can’t go back.
Lives were shaken, hearts in pain,
But through the loss, we call His name.

[Verse 2]
I’ve seen the pictures, heard the cries,
Felt the sorrow in their eyes.
But even when the night is long,
I know that faith can keep us strong.

[Chorus]
Oh, pray for those in the storm,
For the lost, for the torn.
Lift them high, hold them close,
Let them feel they’re not alone.
Through the trials, through the rain,
God is there in all the pain.
Oh, pray for those in the storm,
And the ones who must rebuild once more.

[Verse 3]
A town once bright, now turned to dust,
But hope will rise, in Him we trust.
The hands that help, the hearts that give,
Through love and grace, we start to live.

[Verse 4]
When all seems broken, don’t lose sight,
Morning comes after the night.
He calms the waters, stops the wind,
And lifts us up to stand again.

[Chorus]
Oh, pray for those in the storm,
For the lost, for the torn.
Lift them high, hold them close,
Let them feel they’re not alone.
Through the trials, through the rain,
God is there in all the pain.
Oh, pray for those in the storm,
And the ones who must rebuild once more.

[Bridge]
Lord, bring comfort, bring them peace,
Let Your love be their release.
Through the wreckage, through the tears,
Let them know You're always near.

[Chorus]
Oh, pray for those in the storm,
For the lost, for the torn.
Lift them high, hold them close,
Let them feel they’re not alone.
Through the trials, through the rain,
God is there in all the pain.
Oh, pray for those in the storm,
And the ones who must rebuild once more.

[Outro]
We won’t forget, we won’t turn away,
We’ll stand with them, we’ll always pray.
